.TH SMTOP 1 "2026-04-23" "smartmet-monitor" "SmartMet Server"
.SH NAME
smtop \- interactive terminal monitor for SmartMet Server
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B smtop
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B smtop
is a curses dashboard that combines offline access\-log analysis with
live polling of the SmartMet admin plugin and per\-process /proc
inspection. Twelve views are rotated with
.B Tab
or each view\(aqs single\-letter mnemonic (highlighted in red in the
tab label).
.PP
Three of the views are
.I composite
\- they draw multiple panels at once on a single screen, the same way
btop composes CPU + memory + processes + network. The composites are
.B Live
(per\-plugin Graphs + per\-URL table; default startup view),
.B Health
(Caches + Services + Active in\-flight stacked), and
.B Flame
(full\-screen live flamegraph). The remaining nine views are dedicated
single\-panel views (Overview, Graphs, URLs, Caches, Services, Active,
Proc, Logs, Keys) for sortable / filterable interaction. Sparklines and charts use Braille glyphs by default for
2\(mu horizontal density and 4\(mu vertical resolution; pass
.B \-\-ascii
on terminals or fonts that don\(aqt render U+2800..U+28FF properly.
.PP
The URLs panel is the primary view: per\-endpoint request counts,
mean / p50 / p95 / max latency, error rate, bandwidth, and a
per\-URL latency sparkline. Press
.B Enter
to drill into a URL; the detail view shows windowed stats,
a 60\-minute latency sparkline, an exponential histogram, status
code breakdown, and the top API keys calling that URL.
.PP
Data sources run concurrently:
.IP \(bu 2
Log files given with
.BR \-l ,
tailed (\fBtail -F\fP semantics, rotation\-aware).
.IP \(bu 2
Admin\-plugin URLs given with
.BR \-u ,
polled every
.B \-n
seconds (default 2) for cache, service, active\-request and
last\-request data. Endpoint availability and frontend/backend
role are auto\-detected from
.BR ?what=list .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-l \ PATH-OR-GLOB
Access\-log file. May be given multiple times; globs are expanded.
Defaults to
.BR /var/log/smartmet/*-access-log .
.TP
.BI \-u \ URL
Admin\-plugin base URL. Repeatable or comma\-separated; each URL
may be prefixed with a label (\fILABEL=URL\fP). Duplicate labels
are disambiguated with a trailing
.BR #N .
.TP
.BI \-n \ SECONDS
Admin\-plugin poll interval. Default 2.0 seconds.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-logs
Do not tail any log file (rely solely on admin\-plugin
.IR lastrequests ).
.TP
.B \-\-replay
On startup, read the tail of each log file (capped at
.BR \-\-replay\-bytes )
so the dashboard opens with panels populated instead of empty.
.TP
.BI \-\-replay\-bytes \ N
Maximum number of bytes to read per log file when
.B \-\-replay
is in effect. Default 256 MiB. Gzipped rotated files are read in
full regardless of this cap (gzip doesn\(aqt support cheap
seek\-to\-tail).
.TP
.B \-\-include\-rotated
When
.B \-\-replay
is in effect, also read each log file\(aqs rotated siblings — both
.IR <base>\-YYYYMMDD " (uncompressed) and"
.IR <base>\-YYYYMMDD.gz " (compressed) —"
in chronological order. When the same date is present in both states
the
.I .gz
is preferred to avoid double\-counting during a mid\-rotation window.
.TP
.BI \-\-history\-minutes \ N
Per\-minute history retention. Default 60 minutes. Raise to 1440 for
a day, 10080 for a week. Memory grows roughly linearly: ~12 KB per
minute on a 20\-plugin host, so 24 h ≈ 17 MB and 7 d ≈ 120 MB.
Combine with
.B \-\-include\-rotated
to actually retain the historical data being replayed.
.TP
.B \-\-ascii
Render charts with eighth\-block characters instead of Braille.
.TP
.B \-\-perf
Enable the perf sampler in the
.B Proc
panel. Spawns
.B perf record \-F 99 \-g \-p PID \-\- sleep 1
periodically for the focused
.B smartmetd
PID and renders top symbols + a live flamegraph. Adds ~10% CPU
overhead to the target process during the sampling second of each
cycle. Requires
.B perf
installed and either root or
.BR kernel.perf_event_paranoid \ \(<=\ 2 .
.TP
.BI \-\-perf\-interval \ SEC
Full perf cycle in seconds (record 1 s + idle remainder). Default 10.0.
.SH KEYS
.TP
.BR i " / " h " / " f " / " o " / " g " / " u " / " c " / " s " / " a " / " p " / " l " / " k
Jump to a view (composite or single-panel) by mnemonic letter
(highlighted in the tab). Composites:
.I i
Live,
.I h
Health,
.I f
Flame.
.TP
.BR Tab " / " Shift\-Tab
Next / previous panel.
.TP
.BR ? " / " F1
Toggle help overlay.
.TP
.BR Enter
Drill into the selected URL / API key.
.TP
.BR j " / " k " / " n " / " p
Next / previous entry while drilled in.
.TP
.BR /
Filter (URLs, Keys, Logs).
.TP
.BR s " / " S
Cycle sort column forward / backward.
.TP
.BR r
Reverse current sort.
.TP
.BR [ " / " ]
Shrink / grow the time window (1, 5, 15, 60 minutes).
.TP
.BR h " / " t " / " y
Toggle histogram / status / API\-key sections in the URLs drill\-in.
.TP
.BR n " / " N
Next / previous
.B smartmetd
PID in the Proc panel.
.TP
.BR m " / " b " / " i
Toggle time spark mean\(<>p95 / size spark mean\(<>throughput / idle
handlers shown\(<>hidden in the Graphs panel.
.TP
.BR f
Toggle live flamegraph view (Proc panel, requires \-\-perf).
.TP
.BR e " / " E
Export the current panel to CSV / JSON under
.B $SMARTMET_MONITOR_EXPORT_DIR
(default
.BR /tmp ).
.TP
.BR q " / " Ctrl\-C
Quit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B /var/log/smartmet/*-access-log
Default log glob when no
.B \-l
is given.
.TP
.B /usr/bin/smtop
The dashboard binary (and its
.B smartmet\-top
symlink).
.TP
.B /usr/share/smartmet/bstat.sh
Shared library sourced by the offline
.BR bstat ,
.BR bchart ,
.BR burls ,
.BR bstatus " and " bkeys
commands.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bstat (1),
.BR bchart (1),
.BR burls (1),
.BR bstatus (1),
.BR bkeys (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Finnish Meteorological Institute.
